= Installation =
To install the latest version of OpenTTD, just download and run the installer for your operating system [http://www.openttd.org/download-stable from here]. It can also be installed from [https://store.steampowered.com/app/1536610/OpenTTD/ Steam], [https://www.gog.com/en/game/openttd GOG], [https://apps.microsoft.com/detail/9ncjg5rvrr1c Microsoft Store], and many Linux package managers.

If you use the installer, on first launch it will ask if you would like to download and install open source graphics. Just select "Yes, download the graphics".

Open source graphics have been available since version 1.0.0 of OpenTTD. There are two official graphics sets:
* [[en/Basesets/OpenGFX2]], the current official [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source open source] graphics set made by the OpenTTD team. These are the graphics automatically downloaded.
* [[en/Basesets/OpenGFX]], the original [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source open source] graphics set made by the OpenTTD team.

OpenTTD can also use the original base graphics from the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transport_Tycoon Transport Tycoon Deluxe] (TTD) CD. As opposed to OpenTTD, TTD is '''not''' free software. To install original TTD graphics, see below.

Open source sound effects (OpenSFX), music (OpenMSX), OpenGFX and OpenGFX2, and other alternate sound, music and graphics base sets can be downloaded using the in-game online content downloader, if you have an internet connection.

